  • Ambiguous ORCiDs
  • Stale organisational units

Certain ORCiDs are associated with more than one author at KTH and sometimes also with several âlocal authority identifiersâ in DiVA.

Note

Note that a KTH author may be associated with zero, one (preferably) or in some cases more than one ORCiDs. However, if more than one KTH author identifier make use of the same ORCiD identifier there are chances that an incorrect affiliation has been detected.

Code 
my_dt <- 
  kthcorpus:::check_ambiguous_use_orcid() |> datatable(
    style = "bootstrap4", # "bootstrap" or "bootstrap4" or "auto" (for bslib)
    class = "table-bordered table-condensed table-sm",
    rownames = FALSE,
    height = "100%",
    escape = FALSE,
    extensions = "RowGroup",
    options = list(
      rowGroup = list(dataSrc = 0),  # if rownames are used, increase index!
      paging = FALSE,
      dom = "iftr"  # display number of records at top
    ),
    selection = "none"
  )

# Available "dom" settings:
# l - length changing input control
# f - filtering input
# t - The table!
# i - Table information summary
# p - pagination control
# r - processing display element

bs4_card(my_dt, "ORCiD Table")

Certain authors have publications that are associated with âclosedâ or no longer valid organisational units at KTH. These authors also have other publications tagged with an âopenâ or valid organisational unit, and have more than 50 publications, so may be âlow hanging fruitâ for retagging.

Note

Note that authors can have made some publications that were tagged with an organisational unit at KTH that is closed (or was closed, at the time, based on the publication date) and therefore is/were not valid. If such an âinvalidâ DiVA organisations was closed more than 1.5 years earlier compared to the publication date, there may be more recent organisational units that are better to use. Candidates for suggested valid organisational units that are associated with other publications from the same author are provided below.
